E AND R AMENDMENTS TO LB 771
Introduced by Guereca, 7, Chairman Enrollment and Review
1 1. Strike the original sections and all amendments thereto and
2 insert the following new sections:
3 Section 1. Section 75-327, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
4 amended to read:
5 75-327 (1) A participating driver shall not provide a ride unless it
6 is a prearranged ride. No person shall be a participating driver for a
7 period of more than twelve hours during each twenty-four-hour period.
8 (2)(a) A transportation network company may offer service for
9 compensation, no charge, or suggested compensation.
10 (b) Except as provided in this section, transportation network
11 companies shall not be subject to rate regulation by the commission and
12 shall not be subject to provisions relating to rates and charges
13 prescribed in sections 75-101 to 75-158.
14 (c) A transportation network company shall file with the commission
15 the rates it uses to determine any compensation or suggested compensation
16 on its online-enabled application or platform, including any use of
17 dynamic pricing. The transportation network company shall keep the rate
18 filing current and shall charge rates consistent with the rates it files
19 with the commission.
20 (d) The following requirements apply if the transportation network
21 company uses dynamic pricing through its online-enabled application or
22 platform:
23 (i) The transportation network company's online-enabled application
24 or platform shall provide clear visible indication that dynamic pricing
25 is in effect prior to the passenger requesting a ride;
26 (ii) The transportation network company's online-enabled application
27 or platform shall include a feature that requires the passenger to
-1-

