1 expressly confirm that he or she understands that dynamic pricing will be
2 used in order for the ride request to be completed;
3 (iii) The transportation network company's online-enabled
4 application or platform shall provide a fare estimator that enables the
5 passenger to estimate the cost under dynamic pricing prior to requesting
6 the ride; and
7 (iv) Dynamic pricing shall not be permitted for seven days after any
8 state of emergency declared by the Governor. The prohibition shall be
9 confined to the areas delineated in the Governor's emergency
10 proclamation. The Governor may further regulate dynamic pricing at his or
11 her discretion during any state of emergency through executive order.
12 Dynamic pricing shall not be permitted during any state of emergency
13 declared by the Governor.
14 (3) Upon completion of a prearranged ride, a transportation network
15 company shall transmit an electronic receipt to the passenger's email
16 address or online-enabled application documenting the following:
17 (a) The point of origin and destination of the prearranged ride;
18 (b) The total duration and distance of the prearranged ride;
19 (c) The total amount paid, if any, including the base fare and any
20 additional charges incurred for distance traveled or duration of the
21 prearranged ride; and
22 (d) The driver's first name.
23 Sec. 2. Original section 75-327, Reissue Revised Statutes of
24 Nebraska, is repealed.
25 Sec. 3. Since an emergency exists, this act takes effect when
26 passed and approved according to law.
27 2. On page 1, line 4, strike "and"; and in line 5 after "section"
28 insert "; and to declare an emergency".
